Melania and Donald Trump express their warm greetings to those celebrating Christmas in the United States and around the world. They thank God for blessings and love, and emphasize the importance of coming together as families, friends, and communities to celebrate the birth of Christ. They acknowledge the challenges facing the country, but believe that the bonds that unite Americans are stronger. They encourage fostering a culture of understanding and respect, which reflects the teachings of Christ. They also recognize the religious liberties secured by the forefathers and honor the men and women of the Armed Forces for their service and sacrifice. They hope that people's hearts are filled with love, joy, and faith during Christmas, and send their best wishes for a merry Christmas and a happy New Year.